node.text: Last July, Jessica Turner's husband Matthew shared the "difficult news" that he was gay and that they were ending their 16-year marriage. Jessica grieved the end of their union. "We deeply loved each other," she tells PEOPLE in this week's Family issue, "and didn't want things to be different in terms of our family. But I wanted Matthew to be whole and happy." Despite the feeling of their lives in limbo, the exes have remained best friends through a year of "uncertainty." ❤️ Matthew credits Jessica's unwavering support for their continued bond and his bravery to come out. "It is still really easy to love each other," says Jessica. "That love is different now, but it's beautiful." 🙏 Tap the bio link for their story. | 📷: Alysse Gafkjen

node.text: The COVID-19 variant has given the word "Delta" a negative connotation, but Delta Air Lines is hoping to change that narrative for at least one youngster named Delta. 🙏 "Petition not to call it 'Delta Plus' and instead move on to the next letter in this cursed variant alphabet 😩," the girl's mother Kellie Gerardi tweeted. In response, the Delta Air Lines team sent the 3-year-old a Delta care package. "We hope she knows how much we love her name and how special she should feel," the company tells PEOPLE. ✈️ Tap the bio link for the full story. | 📷: Delta

node.text: While on a break from the road as he supports his latest album, the country star and wife Alexis sat down with PEOPLE for our family issue. ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by People Magazine on August 12, 2021. May be an image of dog.

node.text: After losing her own puppies, a rescue dog found a new family in an orphaned litter. ❤️ Rescue dog Poppy — a new mom who had just given birth to 10 puppies — died unexpectedly at Ruff Start Rescue. Around the same time Poppy died, another rescue dog, Pepper, experienced a tragedy of her own, losing her entire litter of newborn puppies. Pepper was "devastated and grew very depressed" after the death of her puppies, but when volunteers paired up the orphaned newborns with the grieving dog, the new family immediately clicked. 🐶 Tap the bio link for the heartwarming story.

node.text: Rih and A$AP are in it for the long haul. ❤️ The couple's connection "evolved" from a friendship into a "solid romance," a source tells PEOPLE in this week's issue about music's favorite new couple.
